# Source and config: pin to LF so checkouts stay byte-identical across
# macOS, Linux, and Windows. Without this, files committed from a Windows
# host land in the index as CRLF and macOS/Linux working trees show every
# line as a diff (see git ls-files --eol). Run `git add --renormalize .`
# after touching this file to reflow the index.
*.rs       text eol=lf
*.toml     text eol=lf
*.md       text eol=lf
*.yml      text eol=lf
*.yaml     text eol=lf
*.json     text eol=lf
*.sh       text eol=lf
*.txt      text eol=lf

# Frozen patent corpus:
# treat the TIFFs as opaque binary blobs (no diff/merge, no eol normalization)
# and pin the manifest to LF so it stays stable across platforms.
benchmark-corpus/patent-500/files/** binary
benchmark-corpus/patent-500/manifest.tsv text eol=lf